taxon.name: Vanessa cardui

default_photo.attribution: (c) Anna Nicola Chapman, some rights reserved (CC BY)

taxon.wikipedia_summary: Vanessa cardui is a well-known colorful butterfly, known as the painted lady, or in North America as the cosmopolitan. This butterfly has a strange habit of flying in a sort of screw shape.

flags.flag: Project seems ok at first glance, but link to www.iodatabase.eu leads to a porn site.

project.description:
Integrated and Open Database | butterflies

This is the name of a new database for DNA barcodes, occurrences, behavioural and ecological traits of European butterflies.

Here, in iNaturalist, we are collecting occurrences from citizens that want to collaborate to obtain high quality data for the scientific community.


The records are continuously validated by the administrators and are then gathered in the ZEN Lab project.

Photo in the cover by Vlad Dinca.

observation_field.name: Insect life stage
observation_field.description: Insects have a lot of life stages, hopefully we can encapsulate them all here. I doubt I have all of them, so please comment if you want me to add more. Larvae = caterpillars, grubs, maggots, eta. Pupae = chrysalides, etc. Teneral = recently molted adult.
